Package: mantar
Title: Missingness Alleviation for Network Analysis
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Kai Jannik", "Nehler", , "nehler@psych.uni-frankfurt.de", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3764-761X"))
Description: Provides functionality for estimating cross-sectional network structures representing partial correlations in R, while accounting for missing values in the data. Networks are estimated via neighborhood selection or regularization, with model selection guided by information criteria. Missing data can be handled primarily via multiple imputation or a maximum likelihood-based approach; deletion techniques are available but secondary <doi:10.31234/osf.io/qpj35>.
